---
title: 6. Session stickiness — Responses API two-step
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as the embedded assistant UI chat client
    participant G as APIM Gateway
    participant R as Redis<br/>(session cache)
    participant B1 as AOAI backend A
    participant B2 as AOAI backend B

    Note over C,B2: 5a — create
    C->>G: POST /responses (turn 1)
    G->>B1: forward (LB choice)
    B1-->>G: 200 + id=resp_xyz
    G->>R: SET rsp:resp_xyz → backend=A<br/>(TTL 1h)
    G-->>C: 200 + id=resp_xyz

    Note over C,B2: 5b — resume same conversation
    C->>G: POST /responses<br/>previous_response_id=resp_xyz
    G->>R: GET rsp:resp_xyz
    alt session in cache
        R-->>G: backend=A
        G->>B1: pin same backend ✅
        B1-->>G: 200 (context warm)
        G-->>C: 200
    else not found / TTL expired
        R-->>G: nil
        G-->>C: 410 session_expired<br/>(client retries fresh)
    end
